The paper discusses challenges in searching for structured and semi-structured data on the web, which is a topic that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The workshop also aims to improve the user-friendliness of data search, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of algorithms and systems, which could potentially fall under deep learning (cs.DL) if machine learning techniques are employed.
